10/04/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- NATO has sent letters to Albania and Croatia inviting them to launch talks on their accession to the organisation, NATO spokesman James Appathurai announced on Wednesday (April 9th). Both are expected to send delegations to Brussels. Appathurai raised the prospect of formally welcoming the two new members into the Alliance at 60th anniversary celebrations next year. (HRT, Vecernji List, AP, TopChannel, BalkanWeb - 09/04/08)
